Download the ISO:
Visit the Tenable website and download the Tenable Core Nessus installation ISO file.

Mount the ISO:
Open a terminal and navigate to the directory where you downloaded the ISO. Create a directory to mount the ISO and then mount it:

sh

mkdir /mnt/nessus_iso
sudo mount -o loop /path/to/nessus_iso.iso /mnt/nessus_iso

Navigate to the Mounted ISO:
Move to the mounted ISO directory:

sh

cd /mnt/nessus_iso

Run the Installer:
Run the installer script (usually named install.sh) as root or using sudo:

sh

sudo ./install.sh

Follow the Installer Prompts:
The installer will guide you through the installation process. You'll need to accept the license agreement, specify installation directories, and provide administrative credentials.

Start Tenable Core Nessus:
After the installation is complete, you can start the Tenable Core Nessus service:

sh

sudo /etc/init.d/nessusd start

Access the Web Interface:
Open a web browser and navigate to https://localhost:8834. This is the default address for the Tenable Core Nessus web interface.

Initial Configuration:
Follow the on-screen instructions to configure the initial settings, including setting an administrative password.

Activation and Licensing:
If required, activate Tenable Core Nessus by providing the activation code.

Login and Set Up Scans:
Log in to the web interface using the administrative credentials you set. From there, you can configure scans, policies, and manage the security assessments.

Secure and Maintain:
Ensure that Tenable Core Nessus is properly secured, updated, and maintained according to your organization's security policies.
